IRS990.MissionDesc: TO PROVIDE HEALTH CARE SERVICES TO UNDERSERVED COMMUNITIES.
IRS990.Desc: TO PROVIDE QUALITY HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES TO THE MEDICALLY UNDERSERVED AND LOW INCOME POPULATIONS IN A CULTURALLY SENSITIVE MANNER. CENTRAL CITY COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTER, INC. PROVIDES COMPREHENSIVE PRIMARY CARE, DENTAL, OBSTETRICS/GYNECOLOGY, FAMILY PLANNING, MENTAL HEALTH SERVICES, CHIROPRACTIC CARE, FAMILY PRACTICE, PEDIATRICS, PODIATRY, DRUG/HIV/STD TESTING, ONSITE MEDICAL ELIGIBILITY ASSISTANCE, CHRONIC DISEASE MANAGEMENT, AND HIV/AIDS CASE MANAGEMENT SERVICES. SERVICES ARE ALSO CONDUCTED THROUGH SITERUN PREVENTION PROGRAMS, INCLUDING THE COMPREHENSIVE PERINATAL SERVICES PROGRAM, VACCINE FOR CHILDREN PROGRAM, CHILD HEALTH AND DISABILITY PROGRAM, FAMILY PLANNING, ACCESS, CARE AND TREATMENT (FAMILY PACT), AND ITS SOUTH LOS ANGELESBASED MOBILE CLINIC PROVIDES THE SAME CARE TO AREA HOMELESS SHELTERS AND RESIDENTIAL FACILITIES FOR MENTALLY ILL ADULTS. IN FY 2022, 31,791 PATIENTS WERE SERVED AND OVER 190,993 ENCOUNTERS WERE PROVIDED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Sch D, Part X, Line 2:
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE HEALTH CENTER IS A NON-FOR-PROFIT CORPORATION AS DESCRIBED IN SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE (THE "CODE") AND IS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAXES ON RELATED INCOME PURSUANT TO SECTION 501(A)(1) OF THE CODE. THE HEALTH CENTER IS ALSO EXEMPT FROM STATE INCOME TAXES ON RELATED INCOME. ACCOUNTING PRINCIPLES GENERALLY ACCEPTED IN THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA PRESCRIBE REQUIREMENTS FOR THE RECOGNITION OF INCOME TAXES IN FINANCIAL STATEMENTS, AND THE AMOUNTS RECOGNIZED ARE AFFECTED BY INCOME TAX POSITIONS TAKEN BY THE CENTER IN ITS TAX RETURNS. THE HEALTH CENTER'S STATUS AS AN EXEMPT CENTER IS DEFINED AS AN INCOME TAX POSITION UNDER THESE REQUIREMENTS. WHILE MANAGEMENT BELIEVES IT HAS COMPLIED WITH THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE, THE SUSTAINABILITY OF SOME INCOME TAX POSITIONS TAKEN BY THE HEALTH CENTER IN ITS TAX RETURNS MAY BE UNCERTAIN. THERE ARE MINIMUM THRESHOLDS OF LIKELIHOOD THAT UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS ARE REQUIRED TO MEET BEFORE BEING RECOGNIZED IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. MANAGEMENT DOES NOT BELIEVE THAT THE HEALTH CENTER HAS ANY MATERIAL UNCERTAIN TAX POSTIIONS AS OF JUNE 30, 2022, OR 2021. IN THE EVENT INTEREST AND PENALTIES ARE DUE RELATING TO AN UNSUSTAINBALBLE TAX POSTION, THEY WOULD BE TREATED AS A COMPONENT OF INCOME TAX EXPENSE. DURING THE YEARS ENDED JUNE 30, 2022 AND 2021, THERE WERE NO INTEREST OR PENALTIES RELATING TO UNSUSTAINABLE TAX POSTIONS THAT WERE RECONGIZED IN THESE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ONCE A YEAR DURING A BOARD MEETING, EACH BOARD MEMBER IS GIVEN A STATEMENT TO SIGN STATING THERE ARE NO CONFLICTS OF INTEREST THAT HAVE OCCURRED OR WILL OCCUR DURING THE PAST AND SUBSEQUENT TIME REMAINING AS A BOARD MEMBER.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: FOR ALL KEY POSITIONS OF THE ORGANIZATION, THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS OBTAIN AND DOCUMENT THE SALARY SURVEYS THAT HAVE BEEN PREPARED BY INDEPENDENT ORGANIZATIONS. IN ADDITION, THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS OBTAIN SALARY INFORMATION FROM COMPARABLE ORGANIZATIONS TO PROVIDE GUIDANCE IN SETTING THE COMPENSATION OF EACH OF THE POSITIONS. TAKEN INTO CONSIDERATION IN MAKING THE PROPER COMPARISONS ARE THE SIZE AND REVENUES OF THE ORGANIZATIONS. UPON COMPLETE SATISFACTION OF THE COMPARISONS AND SALARY RANGES, THE BOARD MOTIONS TO APPROVE THE COMPENSATION AT THEIR MEETING.
